here’s a reminder that you can choose ANY kind of movement for exercise. it doesn’t have to be at the gym. it doesn’t have to be traditional. it can be a walk. it can be swimming. you can also include a multitude of different types of exercise.

scientific studies show the benefits of exercise. but what kind of exercise is up to you. find something you enjoy. and make it part of your routine. 

certain types of exercise breed certain results, so you can align your training/exercise style to give you specific results. but don’t be discouraged if it takes you a while to find something you like. just get up and move :)

i used to think that my life HAD to look a certain way. that i had to follow a strict path and not deviate. 

it’s tough when you’re young and make these dreams and goals that “by the time i’m 25 i’ll be here and doing this…” and then when you’re not it’s a tough realization. but guess what…that’s okay. it doesn’t mean you’re a failure. we all have different time lines, and there is no ONE perfect way to live. because our life is just that—OURS. 

as i’m getting older i’m listening to my intuition and trying to step away from how i feel like i “need to live my life” and remove myself from that pressure of pleasing everyone and truly stepping into my own. and it is so freeing to finally feel confident that i can create the life i want to live. the possibility’s are endless and there’s no ONE way to do things.

ultimately i’ve learned
-you get rewarded for taking risks. all of my biggest rewards have come from taking the biggest risks and i’m so grateful.
-you’re not truly free until you are being true to yourself 
-your life can be whatever YOU want it to be

just some sentimental thoughts today as i feel like i’m really stepping into myself. i can’t seem to explain it, but i have never been more content. learn to listen and trust yourself. you have so much potential xx

my fitness journey— 🕊️☕️🍂✨ (sorry it’s long!!!)

1. photo taken now
2. 2015 when i started working out with college friends at the gym, i enjoyed being strong and being a bro.

3. 2016 darian and i would workout 3-4 days a week, ate whatever I’d try to cook homemade meals but we weren’t fully invested. we just loved the hobby together.

4. 2018 I decided i wanted to see the hard work I had been putting in at the gym. I wanted to see results. I became a certified personal trainer, studied nutrition and started putting what I learned to work. Majority of the difference was my food intake and i realized nutrition was KEY. *nutrient dense foods first*

5. 2019 darian and I wanted to start a family 🥹 i maintained my habits throughout pregnancy. I tried to workout 3x a week (push, pull, legs) still tried to eat good amounts of fruit, veggie and protein. while also enjoying my cravings. 

6. 2019-2020 we have vinny & my journey starts from the beginning. harder than before. the hardest thing i have done so far. i dealt with a lot of mental health issues, ppd, exhaustion, felt weak and extremely uncomfortable in my own body some days. finding the TIME was near IMPOSSIBLE. let alone energy. i loved my body for what it did for me, darian and Vinny. But I had an identity crisis in who I was. I didn’t feel like myself. then lockdown happened and I felt lost again. 

7. 2020 - I gave myself 9-10 months of grace. knowing that if i tried my best to keep showing up, results would come like they did before. i knew it was a long game. it was about healthy habits, my routine, and i gave myself time to settle back in. worked out 2-3x a week. lots of at home and walks because gyms were closed.

8. gyms opened back up, i started working out with a friend who helped keep me stay accountable and show up on days when I was too tired. (which is every day with a new baby) 

9. after 2 years and a move, i felt like myself again. ready to push myself mentally and physically. THRIVING AGAIN!!!

10. officially a certified muscle mommy 🫡

i am proud to be a mom in the fitness space. i am proud of my body and all it can do and accomplish throughout all of the different phases.

i wouldn’t be able to share this so quickly if i hadn’t already been through hell this year. and it’s not something i can hide or want to. i want to talk about this especially if someone else has been through similar issues. 

on monday darian and i went in for our first ultrasound, 7 weeks pregnant and were so excited. we even saw a rainbow as we were driving honoring our second pregnancy that ended in a traumatic miscarriage earlier this year. (my miscarriage story is for another day, as it has taken me months and months to process it and really only became better once we were pregnant again.)

and while i thought having a miscarriage was the worst thing that had happened to me, this was worse. 

we were told at our ultrasound i had an ectopic pregnancy, and was then immediately rushed to an ER where i was told i needed to have emergency surgery. i sat there on the hospital bed and sobbed as the doctor told me I had to have one of my fallopian tubes removed. heartbroken, shattered, and devastated does not even touch how gut wrenching this day quickly became. what started out as excitement over finally being pregnant again, i came out lost and more broken. more horrible, devastating and traumatic complications occurred while back in surgery that i will not go into detail. but the ectopic pregnancy ruptured and things went down hill. i’m lucky to be here today. :(

the worst case scenario and “what if’s” quickly piled in. 
this was not how i saw my day going, or how this pregnancy would end. 😭

darian was and is my rock through it all. his heart breaks too and watching him also lose this second child is excruciating. and i can’t imagine how helpless he feels through it all. i’m thankful he is in healthcare to walk me through everything and feel so much safer. it will be a long recovery. and even longer mentally and physically after having two worst case scenarios happen in the same year. ❤️‍🩹

we’re saying lots of prayers over our small family and we are trying to have faith that at some point we can keep bringing the cutest kids into this world and our home. we’re just going to try to take this day by day. ❤️‍🩹
